# Small Steps

- Prefer the smallest meaningful change that can be understood and validated.
- Work one causal unit at a time: tests, implementation, and docs for the same behavior change stay together.
- Validate after each substantive change using the closest useful check.
- Do not split work so finely that it creates ceremony without reducing risk.
- Summarize progress at useful checkpoints, not after every trivial action.
